		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Are Druids just 2nd rate clerics at high lvls???<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Jan 15th 1:26 AM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=97952186432700&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=97952186432700&num=3&post=1&replyto=97952186432700"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=97952186432700></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=19838"><span id=>Kega</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>47 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Hello all,<br><br>I wanted to get this communities feedback regarding a comment a good friend of mine made.&nbsp;&nbsp;He has a lvl 35 ranger, a lvl 29 wizard and a couple of other 20-something lvl characters.<br><br>He stated that at high lvls (30+ or so) that druids are really just "2nd rate" healers that ppl will invite into the group when they can't find a "real" cleric to provide healing for the group...  Is this true?  <br><br>He also goes on to state that even though we got DD and Dot spells and damage shields, that the groups request that we don't use them because it is far, far more mana efficient to heal the tanks and let them met out the damage to the mobs, instead of we druids doting or dd'ing the mobs or casting buffs and damage shields on fellow group members...  <br><br>As such, he went on to further state that druids are the biggest requestors of breeze/clarity of any class in the game as in higher lvl groups they are always medding in order to heal the tanks.  Even then he says they can't keep their mana regeneration high enough to do as good a job as a "real" cleric...   How true is all this???  I would be happy to receive any feedback on these issues that anyone might be willing to provide.<br><br>The reason I ask is that I currently have a 13th lvl druid that I am having a blast playing, and can only think that life will start getting much better with SoW, Dot spells at 14th and TP spells at 19th.  But if I am only gonna be a 2nd rate "healer" at higher lvls, then I may need to rethink my decision and start concentrating on my shaman character....  At least he gets better armor and bash...<br><br>Thank you in advance.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Kega, 30th lvl Wood Elf Druid of Povar<br>Kanu, 19th lvl Barbarian Shaman of Povar<br></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >3 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Mon, Jan 15th 5:15 AM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=8&mid=97952186432700&num=3&post=1&replyto=97953560614977"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=97953560614977></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=20015"><span id=Scholar>Muttonchopps</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>40 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I am afraid that your friend is mostly correct.&nbsp;&nbsp;Both Druids and Shaman are considered "2nd Rate" healers at higher levels.  However, when I say "higher levels" I don't mean level 30 plus.  We start to become less desirable as a healer when Clerics get Superior healing at level 34.<br><br>With Greater healing at level 29 we can keep up with Clerics until they get Superior healing at 34.  Unfortunately we don't get our upgrade to Superior Healing until level 53.  Too little too late if you ask me.  Meanwhile Clerics recieve the ultimate healing spell "Complete Heal" at 39.<br><br>So you can see that even a 53 Druid is a second rate healer compared to the cleric at level 39.  In light of this information.. if you wanted to play a druid so that you could be a "1st Rate" healer, I would then suggest that you retire your druid and create yourself a Cleric character.<br><br>Sure.. people will invite you to a group because they couldn't get a Cleric.  I don't have a problem with that.  I wouldn't invite a Paladin, a Shadow Knight or a Ranger to my group if there was a perfectly good Warrior or Monk standing by.  likewise, being a "2nd Rate" healer doesn't neccesarily mean that you will be shunned from groups. People invite me all the time even when there is already a Cleric in the party.  I personally hate trying to pretend I'm a cleric.  I absolutely love to have a healer in the group.  Means I don't have to waste my mana healing.  There are plenty of other things you can do to add your share to a group.  Examples:<br><br>1.  Spirit of Wolf (enhances your groups changes of escaping a pull gone bad)<br>2.  Damage Shields (Tanks love it when monsters beat themselves up)<br>3.  Regen (even clerics don't get hitpoint regeneration spells)<br>4.  Ensare (lessens the chance that a monster will escape and bring back more of his friends).<br>5.  Tracking (you can tell your party members if rare spawns are up in dungeons)<br>6.  Pretty good Damage over Time spells <br>7.  Pretty good Direct Damage Spells<br>8.  Teleports (you facilitate the formation of many group by bring everyone together from distant parts of the world)<br>9.  Back up healer (there are times when even a cleric runs low on mana and may need help.  Sometimes the cleric needs to be healed)<br>10.  Evacuation (when the crap hits the fan people will be thanking the stars that you were on the gun with a well timed evac).<br><br>Think of yourself as a Jack of all trades.  As a druid you are adept at many skills.  Although.. you aren't really the greatest at any single one of those skills.  Still people will like to have you in their group.<br><br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Muttonchopps Ingells<br>54th level Wanderer<br>&lt;Lost Legacy&gt;<br>Test Server</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
